WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.291 --> 00:00:06.200
RETO MEIER: Hi, there.

00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:08.900
My name is Reto Meier, and I'm
usually joined on the App

00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:10.170
Clinic by Ian Ni-Lewis.

00:00:10.170 --> 00:00:12.520
But the preparation for this
week's show required us to do

00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:15.960
some intense physical exercise
in order to properly test

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:18.020
personal fitness
apps Endomondo,

00:00:18.020 --> 00:00:19.870
runtastic, and RunKeeper.

00:00:19.870 --> 00:00:21.650
We chose to test these
apps hiking.

00:00:21.650 --> 00:00:24.290
Now, back in Australia, we call
hiking "walking," but

00:00:24.290 --> 00:00:27.330
folks in California seem to be
more inclined to drive if

00:00:27.330 --> 00:00:30.430
they're going anywhere further
than the nearest car park.

00:00:30.430 --> 00:00:33.120
But in any case, the last time
I saw Ian was deep in the

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:36.380
backwoods of the Big Basin
National Park.

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:40.220
Anyway, find out what features
and technical tips and tricks

00:00:40.220 --> 00:00:45.090
it takes to make a killer
personal fitness app today--

00:00:45.090 --> 00:00:49.270
on "The App Clinic."

00:00:49.270 --> 00:00:52.730
So one of the big benefits of
living in the Bay Area is that

00:00:52.730 --> 00:00:55.830
there's really a limitless
supply of hiking trails all

00:00:55.830 --> 00:00:57.410
within a really short drive.

00:00:57.410 --> 00:01:00.165
Now, being a certified
practicing geek, the only

00:01:00.165 --> 00:01:02.240
thing more fun than hiking
through the wilderness is

00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:04.260
tracking my route
while doing so.

00:01:04.260 --> 00:01:07.090
So all three of today's apps
will let me do that, and a few

00:01:07.090 --> 00:01:09.540
other things as well.

00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:12.390
So all three of today's apps
support a standard set of

00:01:12.390 --> 00:01:15.240
functionality, which is
what I've put up here.

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:17.540
Now, they're all designed to
allow you to track a workout.

00:01:17.540 --> 00:01:19.280
And in this case, they're
optimized for something

00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:22.160
running related, basically any
exercise which can be measured

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:24.650
through a combination of the
distance you've traveled and

00:01:24.650 --> 00:01:26.210
the amount of time it's taken.

00:01:26.210 --> 00:01:28.670
Now, accordingly, they measure
the duration of your workout

00:01:28.670 --> 00:01:30.830
and the distance traveled and
use that to work out things

00:01:30.830 --> 00:01:34.920
like your pace, average speed,
calories burned, water

00:01:34.920 --> 00:01:36.550
consumed, all those
sorts of things.

00:01:36.550 --> 00:01:39.840
And they also use the GPS
information that they track

00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:42.710
throughout your workout to
display your route on a map.

00:01:42.710 --> 00:01:45.840
And each of the apps shows a
slightly different set of

00:01:45.840 --> 00:01:47.690
details on the map
and, in fact, in

00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:49.040
terms of your workout.

00:01:49.040 --> 00:01:51.230
And I'll go through each of
those as we look at the apps

00:01:51.230 --> 00:01:53.030
in a little more detail.

00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:55.190
They each also allow you to
select the activity that

00:01:55.190 --> 00:01:57.030
you're doing and choose from
a selection of different

00:01:57.030 --> 00:01:59.500
workouts, so that could be
running, jogging, rowing,

00:01:59.500 --> 00:02:02.020
cycling, push-ups, whatever
you like.

00:02:02.020 --> 00:02:04.070
And there's different styles
of workouts as well.

00:02:04.070 --> 00:02:06.570
So it could be a one-off,
a time trial versus your

00:02:06.570 --> 00:02:09.620
friends, any number of different
workout styles.

00:02:09.620 --> 00:02:11.590
And again, I'll show you what
some of these apps have to

00:02:11.590 --> 00:02:14.510
offer as we go through
them in detail.

00:02:14.510 --> 00:02:18.320
So taking these features as a
baseline, as a given, this is

00:02:18.320 --> 00:02:20.860
basically what your personal
fitness tracking app needs to

00:02:20.860 --> 00:02:23.930
have in order to
be in the game.

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:25.830
Let's take a look at some of the
features that can really

00:02:25.830 --> 00:02:28.300
help differentiate those apps
from their competitors.

00:02:28.300 --> 00:02:32.250
So this is my wish list of
things that I'd like to see in

00:02:32.250 --> 00:02:34.020
personal fitness apps.

00:02:34.020 --> 00:02:36.070
So there's a bunch of stuff on
this list that's totally in

00:02:36.070 --> 00:02:37.790
the nice-to-have territory.

00:02:37.790 --> 00:02:41.125
So things like a rich tablet
experience and analytics are

00:02:41.125 --> 00:02:43.570
the sort of that can really lift
an app well beyond its

00:02:43.570 --> 00:02:46.230
competitors, well beyond sort of
what you would expect from

00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:49.610
an app, which is really going to
help you win over fans, win

00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:52.420
over users, which are going to
be coming back to your app and

00:02:52.420 --> 00:02:54.250
really become addicted to it.

00:02:54.250 --> 00:02:56.910
But let's face it, these
features are the sorts of

00:02:56.910 --> 00:02:59.080
things which people aren't going
to notice straightaway.

00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:02.490
They're going to require a
certain amount of discovery.

00:03:02.490 --> 00:03:03.510
Now, why is that important?

00:03:03.510 --> 00:03:07.330
Well, as it happens, I was
hiking in Rancho San Antonio a

00:03:07.330 --> 00:03:09.480
couple of weeks ago when my wife
asked me if there was a

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:12.390
way that we could track how far
we were going and how long

00:03:12.390 --> 00:03:14.640
we would be hiking for.

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:16.390
And I thought, you know what?

00:03:16.390 --> 00:03:18.210
There's probably some apps
to help with that.

00:03:18.210 --> 00:03:20.310
So I jumped straight on to our
suggestions on the Trello

00:03:20.310 --> 00:03:23.310
board and installed the first
three apps that were there,

00:03:23.310 --> 00:03:24.960
and that is, in fact,
the three apps which

00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:26.740
we're looking at today.

00:03:26.740 --> 00:03:29.060
Now, the factors that I used
to decide which app we were

00:03:29.060 --> 00:03:31.670
going to actually keep running
was how quickly it let me get

00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:34.270
started with the confidence that
it was going to record

00:03:34.270 --> 00:03:36.070
everything that I
wanted it to.

00:03:36.070 --> 00:03:38.320
So a quick startup and
an intuitive--

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:39.220
dare I say--

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:42.710
obvious controls were
really critical.

00:03:42.710 --> 00:03:44.480
So the overall look and
feel were really

00:03:44.480 --> 00:03:46.250
important here as well.

00:03:46.250 --> 00:03:48.490
I opened each app and literally
spent 5 seconds

00:03:48.490 --> 00:03:50.600
looking at each of them before
I chose which one I was going

00:03:50.600 --> 00:03:52.420
to go with.

00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:54.940
So that gives you a really
good idea of just how

00:03:54.940 --> 00:03:57.660
important it is to make that
great first impression.

00:03:57.660 --> 00:04:00.270
I'm not alone in the way
that I look at my apps.

00:04:00.270 --> 00:04:02.510
People will just download them
and figure, well, which of

00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:03.850
these three am I going to use?

00:04:03.850 --> 00:04:06.370
Eh, this one kind of looks like
it's the best, so they're

00:04:06.370 --> 00:04:07.750
going to go with it.

00:04:07.750 --> 00:04:12.400
So in the end, for me, I ended
up choosing Endomondo.

00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:15.480
So they've got a beautiful
feature page here, which has a

00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:17.160
